    Veterans Health MIT Hacking Medicine 2024

    Hosted by Tampa VAMC; Powered by Microsoft Artificial Intelligence Technology

    May 17 - 19, 2024 at University of South Florida

    Apply Today!

    Creating Solutions to Veterans' Health Challenges

    Calling all innovators, makers, design-obsessives, scientists, nurses, doctors, entrepreneurs, programmers, engineers, researchers, artists, UX & CX, health care futurists and more. Join us in making a difference for Veterans. This event brings top minds together from VA, academia, and public and private sectors to reimagine Veteran health care. Experienced mentors join subject matter experts to guide “hackers” through this opportunity to revolutionize the care we provide for Veterans.

    Interested Participants

    Up to 300 participants working directly on solutions will be drawn primarily from Florida's VA Health Systems (VISN 8), their academic affiliates, and the Tampa Bay community. Additional hackers will be selected nationally through a competitive process to ensure a diversity of backgrounds and expertise.

    Complete an Application

    Innovate for Impact:

    Veterans Health MIT Hacking Medicine Hackathon

    The Veteran Health Hackathon is a three-day event where participants are teamed up with diverse peers and expert mentors. Equipped with a suite of development tools and access to unique VA aggregated datasets, the aim is to collaboratively devise conceptual solutions to solve critical health challenges encountered by Veterans.

    Join Us May 17, 2024 to May 19, 2024

    University of South Florida
    Morsani College of Medicine & Heart Institute
    Tampa, FL

    What to Expect

    Track Selection

    Hackers will be assigned tracks based on their application. Each hacker will have the opportunity to express interest in their preferred tracks in the application.

    Open Invitation

    The Hackathon is open to the public and VA employees, allowing participation outside of regular VA duties.

    Teammate Selection

    Upon arrival, teams will self-form through problem pitches and will stay together throughout the event.

    Application Process

    Applications are continuously reviewed and accepted, with final notifications by May 1st.

    Inclusive Participation

    No special skills, talents, or background are required for individuals to participate.

    Strategic Focus:

    VHA Hackathon Targets Key Priorities for Veteran Health

    Veterans Health – MIT Hacking Medicine 2024 focuses exclusively on Veteran health priorities selected from VHA’s top strategic areas, including the delivery of the best and soonest care using Artificial Intelligence (AI).

    Hackathon Application

    Interested Participants

    Revolutionize Veteran health care in a dynamic three-day event! Collaborate with diverse peers and expert mentors to devise innovative solutions for health challenges faced by Veterans.

    We’re here anytime, day or night - 24/7

    If you are a Veteran in crisis or concerned about one, connect with our caring, qualified responders for confidential help. Many of them are Veterans themselves.

    • Call 1-800-273-8255 and press 1
    • Text to 838255
    • Chat confidentially now
    • Call TTY if you have hearing loss 1-800-799-4889

    Get more resources at VeteransCrisisLine.net.
